OL,3,CConsumer confidence stabilises as Gen
OL,4,CZ prepares to spend
OL,6,F"In a matter of weeks, retailers
OL,7,Fgrapple with the reality of billions
OL,8,Fin extra costs from the increases to
OL,9,Femployer national insurance and the
OL,10,Fnational living wage.
OL,12,F"This #5 billion in new costs will
OL,13,Fgive many no option but to push prices
OL,14,Fup. Food inflation is likely to hit 5%
OL,15,Fby the end of the year, and with
OL,16,Ffurther costs from the new packaging
OL,17,Ftax and implementation of the
OL,18,FEmployment Rights Bill, prices risk
OL,19,Fbeing pushed up further.
